  "body": "Hello. \r\nI am using the openZeppelin \"openzeppelin-solidity\": \"2.0.0-rc.1\", in my dApp project.\r\nAs I am testing it with truffle, I have experienced a bug/ or wrong code description.\r\n(I am unable to copy-paste the code due to copy-rights).\r\nBasically the unit tests fail when attempting to do these 3 steps:\r\n1. Mint a token from accounts[0]  OK\r\n2. ERC721.approve (accounts[1], token, {from:accounts[0]); OK\r\n//at this point accouns[0] owns the token and accounts[1] is approved.\r\n3. From the description of `ERC721`\r\n`safeTransferFrom : Requires the msg sender to be the owner, approved, or operator`\r\nsafeTransferFrom(accounts[1], accounts[2], tokenId, {from: accounts[1]});\r\n//fails here. If I change the sender & _from to accounts[0] works fine. But I want to test the approved account usability as it's stated in description.\r\nThanks.\r\n**üíª 2.0.0-rc.1 / latest truffle as of 10 Nov 2018**\r\n\r\n<!-- Tell us what version of OpenZeppelin you're using, and how you're using it: Truffle, Remix, etc. -->\r\n\r\n**üìù **\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the problem you have been experiencing in more detail. Include as much information as you think is relevant. Keep in mind that transactions can fail for many reasons; context is key here. -->\r\n\r\n**üî¢ Code to reproduce bug**\r\n\r\n<!-- We will be able to better help if you provide a minimal example that triggers the bug. -->\r\n",
